Experts analyzed reports from the Ministry of the Interior and Rosstat, criminal records and public data from gun portals.
The vast majority of illegal weapons, the researchers explain, come from the army and law enforcement.
Half of the weapons on the black market ended up there “due to employees whose work is related to weapons,” the report said.
According to the researchers, 17% of weapons come from places of military conflict, 14% are stolen at the time of manufacture and 5% are from "illegal excavations".
