Furthermore, no article expressly guarantees equality between men and women.
Instead, another article forbids insulting or defaming the Prophet Muhammad or his envoys.
However, the article does not define what an offence is or how it should be punished.
Equally dubious is the wording suggesting that it is forbidden to "offend people".
Is it enough to draw a caricature of the president or to tell a joke at the expense of a lawman?
Many points are therefore to be interpreted in the draft that Morsi submits to the vote and which, in his own words, will be the subject of a referendum among the Egyptians "very soon".
