More than 1,000 women were killed in the state of Mexico while Mr. Pena Nieto was governor, a much higher rate than in the very violent city of Ciudad Juarez - a place notorious for the number of innocent women killed there.
Mr. Pena Nieto’s detractors say that at best he failed to curb the problem of murders committed against women when he was in office.
