Those who knock our ears off never compromise anything, on the contrary, we, the South Americans, have all signed it.
“It is incomprehensible that the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights is in Washington under U.S. funding,” he said, referring to Ecuador’s political asylum granted to WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange.
