It is possible that his physical and mental health is deteriorated by being locked in a small space without being able to do outdoor exercises.
“It affects anyone’s health,” he concludes.
Correa notes that the asylum solution granted to Assange since June in the Ecuadorian embassy in London, which would be the assignment of a safe-haven that would allow him to travel to Ecuador, is in the hands of Britain, Sweden and the European judicial authorities.
We do not negotiate with human rights, we do not use that word in this case, but there have been ongoing discussions.
